-- Officer Who Responded at Temple Was Ambushed, Police Say
-- B y   D a n   H a r t
-- 2012-08-05T21:15:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-05/officer-who-responded-at-temple-was-ambushed-police-say.html
The first police officer who
responded to 911 calls at the Sikh temple in Oak Creek,
Wisconsin, was ambushed by the alleged shooter, police said.  A second police officer then shot and killed the gunman,
said  John Edwards , police chief for the Oak Creek police
department, in a televised briefing.  Seven were killed in the shooting and three were injured,
including the police officer, Edwards said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dan Hart at 
 dahart@bloomberg.net  